I am trying to read the current draw of our REV Power Distribution Panel, but I am unsure if I need to import a class I am missing, or if I just have no idea what i’m doing.(I’m leaning towards the latter) The line I pointed out has red squigglies that announce “PowerDistributionPanel cannot be resolved to a type”
Any help is appreciated
package frc.robot;

import edu.wpi.first.wpilibj.TimedRobot;
//import edu.wpi.first.wpilibj.Timer; hehe
import edu.wpi.first.wpilibj.drive.DifferentialDrive;
import edu.wpi.first.wpilibj.Joystick;
import edu.wpi.first.wpilibj.PowerDistribution;
import edu.wpi.first.wpilibj.smartdashboard.SmartDashboard;
import com.revrobotics.CANSparkMax;
import com.revrobotics.CANSparkMaxLowLevel.MotorType;

public class Robot extends TimedRobot {
private PowerDistributionPanel examplePDP = new PowerDistributionPanel(0); <------

private Functions config = new Functions();
private CANSparkMax leftMotor;
private CANSparkMax rightMotor;
private static final int leftMotorID = 1;
private static final int rightMotorID = 2;
private DifferentialDrive robotDrive;
Joystick stick = new Joystick(0);

@Override

Hey there,

PowerDistributionPanel is part of CTRE. Since you are using REV, you should use the built-in WPILib class: Power Distribution Module — FIRST Robotics Competition documentation

PowerDistribution examplePD = new PowerDistribution(1, ModuleType.kRev);

Make sure your CAN ID is defaulted on the PDH (set to 1)
